players.name: Farid Ouédraogo
players.summary: Soufian Farid Ouédraogo is a Burkinabé professional footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for AS Vita Club and the Burkina Faso national team.

players.name: Hervé Koffi
players.summary: Kouakou Hervé Koffi is a Burkinabé professional footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for French Ligue 1 club Angers on loan from Lens, and the Burkina Faso national team.

players.name: Kilian Nikiema
players.summary: Killian Basba Geeke Nikiema is a professional footballer who plays as goalkeeper for ADO Den Haag. Born in the Netherlands, he plays for the Burkina Faso national team.

players.name: Abdoul Ayinde
players.summary: Abdoul Rachid Ayinde is a Burkinabé professional footballer who plays as a left-back for the Belgian Pro League club Gent, and the Burkina Faso national team.

players.name: Adamo Nagalo
players.summary: Adamo Nagalo is a professional footballer who plays as a centre-back for Eredivisie club PSV Eindhoven. Born in the Ivory Coast, he represents Burkina Faso at international level.

players.name: Nasser Djiga
players.summary: Yacouba Nasser Djiga is a Burkinabé professional footballer who plays as a centre-back for Scottish Premiership club Rangers, on loan from Premier League club Wolverhampton Wanderers, and the Burkina Faso national team.

players.name: Issa Kaboré
players.summary: Issa Kaboré is a Burkinabé professional footballer who plays as a right-back or right wing-back for EFL Championship club Wrexham, on loan from Premier League club Manchester City, and the Burkina Faso national team.

players.name: Edmond Tapsoba
players.summary: Edmond Fayçal Tapsoba is a Burkinabé professional footballer who plays as a centre-back for Bundesliga club Bayer Leverkusen and the Burkina Faso national team.

players.name: Issoufou Dayo
players.summary: Issoufou Sellsavon Dayo is a Burkinabé professional footballer who plays as a centre-back for Umm Salal and the Burkina Faso national team. Issoufou Dayo featured in the AFCON 2021 third place match against Cameroon.

players.name: Saïdou Simporé
players.summary: Saïdou Simporé is a Burkinabé professional footballer who used to play as a right back for Egyptian Premier League side National Bank of Egypt SC.

players.name: Steeve Yago
players.summary: Steeve Farid Yago is a professional footballer who plays as a defender for Cypriot First Division club Aris Limassol. Born in France, he represents the Burkina Faso national team.

players.name: Arsène Kouassi
players.summary: Kan Guy Arsène Kouassi is a professional football player who plays as a left-back for French Ligue 1 club Lorient and the Burkina Faso national team. Born in the Ivory Coast, he made his debut for the Burkina Faso national team in 2025.

players.name: Mohamed Zougrana
players.summary: Mohamed Tchapi Zougrana is a professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for MC Alger in the Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1. Born in Ivory Coast, Zougrana represents the Burkina Faso national team.

players.name: Cedric Badolo
players.summary: Cédric Badolo is a Burkinabé professional footballer who plays for Slovak club Spartak Trnava as an attacking midfielder.

players.name: Abdoul Yoda
players.summary:
Abdoul Yoda may refer to:Karim Yoda, French footballer
Abdoul Yoda, Burkinabé footballer

players.name: Stephane Aziz Ki
players.summary: Stephane Aziz Ki is a professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for Botola Pro club Wydad. Born in the Ivory Coast, he plays for the Burkina Faso national team.

players.name: Ismahila Ouédraogo
players.summary: Wandepanga Ismahila Ouédraogo is a Burkinabé professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for Odense Boldklub and the Burkina Faso national team.

players.name: Gustavo Sangaré
players.summary: Gustavo Fabrice Sangaré is a Burkinabé professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for Armenian Premier League club Noah and the Burkina Faso national team.

players.name: Blati Touré
players.summary: Ibrahim Blati Touré is a Burkinabé professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for Egyptian Premier League club Pyramids FC and the Burkina Faso national team.

players.name: Josué Tiendrébéogo
players.summary: Wendkuuni Josué Tiendrébéogo is a Burkinabé professional football player who plays as an attacking midfielder for Annecy and the Burkina Faso national team.

players.name: Lassina Traoré
players.summary: Lassina Chamste Soudine Franck Traoré is a Burkinabé professional footballer who plays as a forward for Ukrainian Premier League club Shakhtar Donetsk and the Burkina Faso national team.

players.name: Dango Ouattara
players.summary: Dango Aboubacar Faissal Ouattara is a Burkinabé professional footballer who plays as a winger or wing-back for Premier League club Brentford and the Burkina Faso national team.

players.name: Bertrand Traoré
players.summary: Bertrand Isidore Traoré is a Burkinabé professional footballer who plays as a forward or a right winger for Premier League club Sunderland and captains the Burkina Faso national team.

players.name: Ousseni Bouda
players.summary: Ousseni Bouda is a Burkinabé professional footballer who plays for Major League Soccer club San Jose Earthquakes and the Burkina Faso national team.

players.name: Mohamed Konaté
players.summary:
Mohamed Konaté may refer to:Mohamed Konaté, Malian footballer
Mohamed Konaté, Ivorian-Burkinabé footballer

players.name: Georgi Minoungou
players.summary: Georgi Minoungou is a professional footballer who plays as a winger for Major League Soccer club Seattle Sounders FC. Born in Ivory Coast, he represents the Burkina Faso national team.

players.name: Cyriaque Irié
players.summary: Cyriaque Kalou Bi Irié is a Burkinabé professional footballer who plays as a forward for German Bundesliga club SC Freiburg. Born in the Ivory Coast, he plays for the Burkina Faso national team.

players.name: Pierre Landry Kaboré
players.summary: Pierre Landry Kaboré is a Burkinabé professional footballer who plays for Scottish Premiership side Heart of Midlothian, as a winger or forward. He has also represented Burkina Faso at international level.
